        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 5:46PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 546 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Harrisburg, or 18 miles southwest of Scottsbluff, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gering, Harrisburg, Wildcat Hills State Recreation Area, Hubbard
Hill, Scotts Bluff National Monument, and Wrights Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
